    "faq-adapters": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "cat-adapters": {
          "type": "rich-text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "CarPlay Adapters"
          }
        },
        "q1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does my car need factory CarPlay to use an AutoLinkr adapter?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. AutoLinkr Pro™, Elite™, and Base™ adapters require factory-installed wired CarPlay. They convert your wired CarPlay connection to wireless — they do NOT add CarPlay to vehicles that don't already have it.</p><p>Not sure if your car has CarPlay? Check your vehicle's settings menu or visit our <a href='/pages/compatibility'>Compatibility Checker</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What's the difference between AutoLinkr Base, Pro, and Elite?",
            "text": "<p><strong>AutoLinkr Base™ ($69.99):</strong> Wireless CarPlay only. No streaming apps. Best for drivers who just want wireless convenience.</p><p><strong>AutoLinkr Pro™ ($79.99):</strong> Wireless CarPlay + Netflix, YouTube, and Google Play Store. Best value for most drivers.</p><p><strong>AutoLinkr Elite™ ($199.99):</strong> Everything in Pro + split-screen multitasking + faster CPU processor. Our most advanced model for power users.</p><p>We always recommend upgrading from Pro to Elite — the Elite handles two apps simultaneously and runs significantly faster.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I set up my AutoLinkr adapter?",
            "text": "<p>Setup takes under 60 seconds:</p><ol><li>Plug the AutoLinkr adapter into your factory CarPlay USB port.</li><li>Your car screen will prompt you to connect.</li><li>Enable Bluetooth and Wi-Fi on your iPhone and follow the on-screen pairing prompts.</li><li>Once paired, every future drive connects automatically — no repeat steps ever.</li></ol><p>No apps or accounts required for initial setup.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will it work with my iPhone?",
            "text": "<p>AutoLinkr adapters are compatible with iPhone 7 and newer running iOS 10 or above. This covers virtually all iPhones in use today.</p><p>We recommend keeping your iPhone's iOS up to date for the best wireless CarPlay performance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does AutoLinkr work with Android phones?",
            "text": "<p>AutoLinkr Pro™, Elite™, and Base™ are designed for Apple CarPlay (iPhone only). Android Auto is not supported by these adapters.</p><p>For Android users — or anyone without factory CarPlay — the <a href='/products/autolinkr-dash'>AutoLinkr Tablet™</a> is our standalone portable CarPlay solution that works with any car and any phone setup.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I stream Netflix and YouTube while driving?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — AutoLinkr Pro™ and Elite™ unlock streaming apps including Netflix, YouTube, and the Google Play Store directly on your factory car screen.</p><p>Streaming is powered through your iPhone's cellular hotspot or a Wi-Fi connection. Video streaming is intended for use while parked or by passengers. As the driver, always keep your eyes on the road and follow local traffic laws.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q7": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What apps can I use with AutoLinkr Pro and Elite?",
            "text": "<p>AutoLinkr Pro™ and Elite™ include access to the Google Play Store, giving you a wide range of apps beyond just streaming. Popular uses include:</p><ul><li><strong>Streaming:</strong> Netflix, YouTube, Disney+, Hulu, Spotify</li><li><strong>Navigation:</strong> Waze, Google Maps, HERE Maps</li><li><strong>Music:</strong> Spotify, Amazon Music, Tidal</li><li><strong>Communication:</strong> WhatsApp, messaging apps (for passengers)</li></ul><p>As a CarPlay device, the standard iOS apps (Apple Maps, Apple Music, Podcasts, Messages, etc.) continue to work as normal.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q8": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is split-screen and why does Elite have it?",
            "text": "<p>Split-screen multitasking lets you run two apps side by side on your factory car screen at the same time. For example, you can have navigation on one half and music on the other — simultaneously.</p><p>The AutoLinkr Elite™ is the only model that supports split-screen. It also features a faster processor that makes everything run smoother when multitasking. If you want the full power experience, Elite is worth the upgrade.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q9": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do I need an internet connection to use streaming apps?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, streaming apps like Netflix and YouTube require an active data connection. You can use:</p><ul><li>Your iPhone's mobile hotspot (Personal Hotspot)</li><li>A public or home Wi-Fi network if available</li></ul><p>Standard cellular data plans work fine. Most streaming apps offer a lower-quality SD mode that's lighter on data usage.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q10": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will my car's screen resolution look the same?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. AutoLinkr adapters maintain the native resolution of your factory screen. There is no reduction in display quality compared to wired CarPlay.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q11": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does it drain my car battery?",
            "text": "<p>No. The AutoLinkr adapter draws power from your car's USB port and only runs when the car is on. It powers off automatically when you shut the engine. There is no risk of battery drain from the adapter itself.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q12": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will it void my car's warranty?",
            "text": "<p>No. AutoLinkr adapters plug into your car's existing USB port — there is no permanent modification, cutting of wires, or alteration to your vehicle. This is the equivalent of plugging in a USB device. It does not affect your car's warranty.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
