    "faq-dash": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "cat-dash": {
          "type": "rich-text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "AutoLinkr Dash™ Cam"
          }
        },
        "dq1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does the dash cam work with any car?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. The AutoLinkr Dash™ is a universal dash cam that works with any vehicle that has a 12V power outlet (cigarette lighter socket). No special car compatibility or existing CarPlay is required.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dq2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What SD card size should I get?",
            "text": "<p>We offer three options:</p><ul><li><strong>No SD Card:</strong> Best if you already own a Class 10 microSD card (supports up to 128GB).</li><li><strong>32GB (included):</strong> Approximately 4–6 hours of dual 1080P footage. Perfect for daily driving and commuters.</li><li><strong>64GB (included):</strong> Approximately 8–10 hours of dual 1080P footage. Ideal for long road trips, rideshare drivers, or maximum coverage.</li></ul><p>With loop recording, old footage is automatically overwritten when the card is full, so continuous protection is always maintained.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dq3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does the rear camera record in HD too?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — both the front and rear cameras record in Full 1080P HD simultaneously. The rear camera connects via the included cable routed along your headliner to the rear window.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dq4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I access and download my footage?",
            "text": "<p>You have three options:</p><ol><li><strong>WiFi App:</strong> Use the free AutoLinkr app (iOS & Android) to connect wirelessly and download clips to your phone.</li><li><strong>SD Card Reader:</strong> Remove the microSD card and use any USB card reader on your computer.</li><li><strong>Built-In Display:</strong> View footage directly on the camera's built-in LCD screen.</li></ol>"
          }
        },
        "dq5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the G-sensor and what does it do?",
            "text": "<p>The G-sensor detects sudden impacts, sharp braking, or collisions. When triggered, it automatically locks the current footage file so it cannot be overwritten by loop recording. This ensures critical evidence footage is always preserved — even if you're unaware an incident occurred.</p><p>Sensitivity can be adjusted in the app or directly on the camera settings menu.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dq6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can the dash cam record while the car is parked?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. With the included hardwire kit (connects directly to your fuse box), the AutoLinkr Dash™ enters a low-power parking mode that monitors for motion or impacts while your car is parked — even with the engine off. Any motion or collision triggers a recording automatically.</p><p>Using only the 12V cigarette lighter power, the camera records only while the engine is running.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dq7": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How wide is the camera angle?",
            "text": "<p>The front camera features a 170° ultra-wide angle lens, capturing everything in front of and beside your vehicle. The rear camera uses a 150° wide angle. Together they provide near-complete 360° coverage of your vehicle's surroundings.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
