        "cq1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I know if my car has factory CarPlay?",
            "text": "<p>Most cars manufactured after 2016 include factory CarPlay. To check:</p><ol><li>Look in your car's infotainment settings for a 'CarPlay' option</li><li>Try plugging your iPhone into your car's USB port — if it asks to use CarPlay, you have it</li><li>Check your car's manual or visit our <a href='/pages/compatibility'>Compatibility Checker</a> for your specific make and model</li></ol><p>CarPlay is available on over 800 car models across all major brands including Honda, Toyota, Ford, BMW, Mercedes, and more.</p>"
          }
        },
        "cq2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Which car brands and models are compatible?",
            "text": "<p>AutoLinkr Pro™, Elite™, and Base™ work with any car that has a factory-installed wired CarPlay port. This includes virtually all major car brands: Honda, Toyota, Ford, Chevrolet, BMW, Mercedes-Benz, Audi, Hyundai, Kia, Mazda, Subaru, Volkswagen, Nissan, and hundreds more.</p><p>Use our <a href='/pages/compatibility'>Compatibility Checker</a> to confirm your specific vehicle.</p>"
          }
        },
        "cq3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "My car has CarPlay but the USB port is a USB-C. Will it work?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — AutoLinkr includes both USB-A and USB-C connection cables to ensure compatibility with all factory port types. If your car uses USB-C for CarPlay, you are fully covered.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
